Since I’ve gotten new ig followers and I’m home bored I figured I’ll introduce myself. Hello my name is Courtney, I’m 34 years old and I own Tooth & Nail Tattoo. Jan 1st will be our 5 year anniversary. I did my first tattoo on myself when I was 15, which I still have and haven’t really stopped since but I got an actual apprenticeship when I was 18 years old and tried to do things the right way. Tattooing has saved my life in many ways which we won’t get into now but it’s my biggest passion in life and I can’t wait to see where it takes me. Thanks to everyone to gets tattooed by me and my husband and best friends for always loving me. #reel #tattooreel #tattooreels #awesometattoos #bettyboop #stevienicksstyle #stevienicks #eternalink #macericktattoomercentile #blackworkgloves #phucstyxtattoosupply #cttattooer #cttattooartist #ladiesoftattooing #skinartmag #inkedmag #inked

Books open FEB 26th 
But what does that mean?!?!
Feb 26th I’ll have my pal Kyle get onto our shop website and enable my booking form. Feb 26th you’ll will click the website (link in bio) and then select the option “book an appointment” OR “booking form” in the drop down menu. 

You’ll fill out the form with as much info as you can (make sure you click my name on top so the email gets to me). Once you do that I go through all emails and pick the ideas I think I’d be best suited for. Myself or Shea will then call people to set up a consultation so we can speak in person about the design you want, we will pick a day for you to get tattooed (it’ll be in the late spring/ summer and onward) you’ll leave a deposit and we’ll get the damn thing done. 

Thank you as always 🖤

3 years ago today I got a phone call. I was told I had multiple sclerosis. I didn’t even know what that was. I thought I was going to die or end up paralyzed, I had no idea what that meant for my near future. But here I am 3 years later. Not only surviving but thriving. After diagnosis my thoughts were centered on the things I may lose the ability to do, never stopping to focus on the thing I AM doing. You join support groups for comfort but it’s all just people being sad and sharing their grief, which they’re allowed to do but that shit makes you feel worse.
So here is some things I have done WHILE also having MS.
I have celebrated 10 years of love with my husband, I have celebrated 5 years of owning my dream tattoo shop. I have seen my own art in magazines and have become sponsored by my favorite tattooing products. I have traveled with my best friends, even doing my first over seas trip. I have met and made friends with the coolest people. 
I have learned that it’s ok to be vulnerable, I have cried, I have laughed so hard I’ve pissed. I’ve let myself receive love from those who want to take care of me on those days that I need a helping hand. I’ve learned to rest.

Ms takes a lot from you, we all know that. But no one shares how much MS gives back. Here’s to 3 years.

Gotten literally thousands of new followers over the past couple months so lemme reintroduce myself. 

My name is Courtney, Mello is my maiden name… before ig only family would call me Court. It’s honestly still a little weird when strangers call me that but I’m ok with it. 

Anywho the start of how I began tattooing is real shaky.  I tattooed in houses, scratcher shops and kinda…. where ever I could. For the first few 5ish years it was mostly about getting fucked up and numbing myself.

Tattooing is all I know and I’ve dedicated my life to it, in turn  it has rewarded me beyond measure. 

I’ll be 35 in a couple weeks and I’m just now learning (and practicing) being soft. I was never granted that privilege growing up. 

I have multiple sclerosis but I’m doing very well. Getting diagnosed has taught me to enjoy my life more and not be afraid ( I still am sometimes tho)

I take pride in being super ambitious and working until I reach my goals and 

I’m very proud of myself.
Be my friend or not.

📸 @shutter.surprize
